		<summary>
			<description>
				You anesthetized Nick, a 1-year old male intact mixed breed dog, for castration a short time ago. You premedicated with dexmedetomidine (10 ug/kg IM) and hydromorphone (0.1 mg/kg) and induced with propofol. Surgery went smoothly and Nick was extubated 10 minutes ago. You were scrubbing for your next surgery when your technician asked you to come to the treatment area to evaluate Nick. He was just found in his recovery cage and was unresponsive.
			</description>
